RIYADH: Saudi Arabia’s Minister of State for Foreign Affairs and Climate Affairs Envoy Adel bin Ahmed Al-Jubeir received on Wednesday the ambassadors of Mauritius and Kyrgyzstan to the Kingdom in Riyadh, the Saudi Press Agency reported. During the meeting with Mauritius Ambassador Shaukat Ali Soudhan, the two countries discussed bilateral relations and issues of mutual interest. Meanwhile, Al-Jubeir wished success to Ulukbek Maripov in carrying out his role as  the newly appointed Kyrgyz ambassador to Saudi Arabia. 